@T the TAU class hierarchy browser tool
@P
@N
@D blue {-foreground blue}
@D ul {-underline true}
@D button { -foreground black -background grey90 -relief raised -borderwidth 2}

             @{blue {CLASSY}} (CLASS hierarchY browser)

is a @{ul {class hierarchy browser}} for programs written in C++
and C++ based languages. The class hierarchy is displayed
in the @{L {graph display area} {showHelp classy 1.2-display}}. You can invoke some basic
features of the classy tool or change the appearance of
the displayed class hierarchy by using the @{L {menubar} {showHelp classy 1.1-menu}}.

To exit the classy tool use the @{button { Exit }} entry in the
@{button { File }} menu or press the key "Q".
